
                                            Mofokeng announced his resignation on Monday night.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - The Democratic Alliance (DA) in Gauteng has hailed the resignation of Emfuleni Mayor Simon Mofokeng as a victory in the fight against women and child abuse. Mofokeng announced his resignation on Monday night. He's accused of sexually assaulting and grooming a 14-year-old girl. The DA's Kingsol Chabalala: "As the Democratic Alliance, Emfuleni needs a new beginning. With the processes to appoint a new mayor, we'll also put our candidate forward."